JOHANNESBURG - Traffic is returning to normal along major highways near the OR Tambo International Airport. It follows a protest by meter taxi drivers on Friday morning.They blocked a section of the R24 highway in both directions, near the airport.The protest also affected the R21 highway.READ: Taxi drivers block highway in Uber protestPolice have impounded several vehicles.It s believed drivers are protesting against taxi-hailing platform, Uber. No arrests have been made yet.Meanwhile, Uber is rubbishing claims by some metered taxi operators that it's running an illegal operation.It says drivers blocking roads on Friday don't represent the majority in the metered taxi industry.eNCA